# Keep scripts/setup.sh Up-to-Date

`scripts/setup.sh` is the single entry point for fresh-environment setup. It must stay in sync with what CI and development actually require.

## When to Update

**Whenever you change any of the following**, update `scripts/setup.sh` in the same step:

| Change | Update in setup.sh |
|--------|--------------------|
| Node.js version in CI (`.github/workflows/ci.yml`) | `REQUIRED_NODE` / `RECOMMENDED_NODE` |
| New `package.json` scripts or dev deps | Add verification step if new check (e.g. new lint tool) |
| Playwright config or E2E setup | Keep `playwright install --with-deps chromium` or adjust for new browsers |
| `.nvmrc` or `.node-version` added | Read and enforce that version in setup.sh |
| New required system dependency (e.g. `ripgrep`, `ffmpeg`) | Add check + install hint before `npm ci` |
| CI adds a new step (env var, extra tool install) | Mirror the step in setup.sh so local dev matches CI |

## Sync Checklist

Before finishing a change that affects setup:

- [ ] Node version in setup.sh matches CI (`node-version` in `ci.yml`)
- [ ] `npm ci` vs `npm install` logic matches lockfile presence
- [ ] Playwright install command matches CI (browsers, `--with-deps`)
- [ ] Verification steps (format, lint, typecheck, test:unit) match CI order
- [ ] Any new required tool is checked or installed

## Principle

A developer cloning the repo and running `./scripts/setup.sh` should end up with an environment that passes `npm run ci`.
